In 1889 the Cambridgeshire part of the parish of Outwell became 
    a separate parish in the Isle of Ely. See also Table 2, notes (h) and (h).

Abolished 1.4.1935 and divided between the parishes of Tilney St. 
    Lawrence and Marshland St. James.

In 1889 the Cambridgeshire part of the parish of Upwell became 
    a separate parish in the Isle of Ely. See also Table 2, notes (a), (b), 
    (h), (h) and (h).

Renamed 1.4.1974 to become the parish of Wisbech. See also Table 
    2, note (j).
